---
// two-body-split — Chapter 049 Lesson 3, "Readable in every client".
//
// The point this figure cements: ONE React node produces BOTH bodies of a
// `multipart/alternative` message automatically (the SDK derives the text part),
// and the CLIENT — not the author — picks which one to render. That kills the
// instinct to hand-write a parallel text field.
//
// Shape: a single horizontal flow, left to right, reusing the lit/dimmed node
// grammar foreshadowed by L1's render-pipeline diagram —
//
//   <WelcomeEmail />  →  Resend SDK  →  [ multipart/alternative envelope:
//                                          text/html  (chosen, lit)
//                                          text/plain (dimmed) ]  →  Mail client
//
// Both bodies sit inside one envelope box (a fieldset-legend pill on its top
// border) so "they're bundled, not two emails" reads at a glance. The CLIENT's
// choice is the only lit/dimmed signal in the envelope: text/html carries the
// accent + a check (the body most clients render), text/plain is dimmed — the
// caption explains the SDK still generated both.
//
// Engine: plain HTML + CSS (the diagrams index's pick for a color-coded flow,
// and the convention the sibling L2 figure uses). Theme-aware via Starlight CSS
// variables + color-mix on a saturated accent so it reads on both the light and
// dark Figure card. `.not-content` drops Starlight prose styling. On a wide
// Figure the strip is one row; below ~560px it stacks vertically and the chevrons
// rotate to point down, so it stays clean on mobile instead of orphaning an
// arrow on a flex-wrap. <Figure> + caption are supplied by the MDX, not here.

const ALT =
  'Flow: the WelcomeEmail React node feeds the Resend SDK, which renders and packs both bodies into one multipart/alternative envelope holding a text/html body and a text/plain body; a mail client at the end renders the text/html body and skips the text/plain one.';
---

<div class="tbs not-content" role="img" aria-label={ALT}>
  {/* 1 · The single source: the react node you pass to send. */}
  <div class="tbs-node">
    <span class="tbs-node-title tbs-mono">{'<WelcomeEmail />'}</span>
    <span class="tbs-node-role">the react node</span>
  </div>

  <div class="tbs-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</div>

  {/* 2 · The SDK renders it and packs both bodies. */}
  <div class="tbs-node">
    <span class="tbs-node-title">Resend SDK</span>
    <span class="tbs-node-role">renders + packs both</span>
  </div>

  <div class="tbs-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</div>

  {/* 3 · One envelope, two bodies bundled inside it. */}
  <div class="tbs-env">
    <span class="tbs-env-legend tbs-mono">multipart/alternative</span>

    <div class="tbs-body tbs-body-chosen">
      <span class="tbs-status tbs-status-on" aria-hidden="true">✓</span>
      <span class="tbs-mono tbs-body-type">text/html</span>
      <span class="tbs-body-note">rich layout</span>
    </div>

    <div class="tbs-body tbs-body-skipped">
      <span class="tbs-status tbs-status-off" aria-hidden="true">–</span>
      <span class="tbs-mono tbs-body-type">text/plain</span>
      <span class="tbs-body-note">auto-derived</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="tbs-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</div>

  {/* 4 · The client renders exactly one of the two. */}
  <div class="tbs-node">
    <span class="tbs-node-title">Mail client</span>
    <span class="tbs-node-role">renders whichever it can</span>
  </div>
</div>

<style>
  /* The single accent hue carries "this is lit / live": a saturated indigo that
     reads on both themes via color-mix, matching the chapter's accent feel. */
  .tbs {
    --tbs-accent: var(--sl-color-text-accent, #4f46e5);
    margin: 0;
    box-sizing: border-box;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    align-items: stretch;
    justify-content: center;
    column-gap: 10px;
    row-gap: 14px;
    max-width: 720px;
    margin-inline: auto;
    font-family: var(--sl-font-system, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif);
  }
  .tbs * {
    box-sizing: border-box;
  }
  .tbs-mono {
    font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, monospace;
  }

  /* ── A plain node (the react node, the SDK, the client) ─────────────────────
     Every node here is "lit" — each is a live stage of the one pipeline: an
     accent-tinted card with a confident border and a stacked title + role. */
  .tbs-node {
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 3px;
    width: 132px;
    padding: 12px 10px;
    text-align: center;
    border-radius: 10px;
    border: 1.5px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--tbs-accent) 55%, transparent);
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--tbs-accent) 12%, var(--sl-color-bg, #fff));
  }
  .tbs-node-title {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 13.5px;
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: var(--sl-color-white, #1e293b);
  }
  .tbs-node-role {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 11px;
    line-height: 1.3;
    color: var(--sl-color-gray-3, #64748b);
  }

  /* ── The connecting chevron ───────────────────────────────────────────────
     Its own flex child, vertically centred against the node cards. */
  .tbs-arrow {
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    align-self: center;
    font-size: 20px;
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--sl-color-gray-3, #94a3b8);
  }

  /* ── The multipart/alternative envelope ────────────────────────────────────
     One outer box that visually CONTAINS both bodies — "bundled, not two
     emails". A fieldset-legend pill straddles its top border to name it. */
  .tbs-env {
    position: relative;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 8px;
    width: 196px;
    padding: 18px 12px 12px;
    border-radius: 12px;
    border: 1.5px dashed var(--sl-color-gray-4, #b0b7c3);
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sl-color-gray-5, #94a3b8) 9%, var(--sl-color-bg, #fff));
  }
  /* Block + fit-content + 50% negative translate straddles the border; the bg
     matches the Figure card so it "breaks" the dashed line. */
  .tbs-env-legend {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
    margin: 0;
    display: block;
    width: fit-content;
    padding: 1px 8px;
    border-radius: 999px;
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.4;
    white-space: nowrap;
    color: var(--sl-color-gray-2, #475569);
    background: var(--sl-color-bg-sidebar, #f7f8fa);
    border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-4, #b0b7c3);
  }

  /* ── A body box inside the envelope ────────────────────────────────────────
     Both bodies are real/present (the SDK generated both). The only signal is
     the CLIENT's pick: chosen = accent border + check; skipped = muted + dim. */
  .tbs-body {
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    padding: 8px 10px;
    border-radius: 8px;
  }
  .tbs-body-chosen {
    border: 1.5px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--tbs-accent) 60%, transparent);
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--tbs-accent) 14%, var(--sl-color-bg, #fff));
  }
  .tbs-body-skipped {
    border: 1.5px solid var(--sl-color-gray-5, #d0d5dd);
    background: var(--sl-color-bg, #fff);
    opacity: 0.55;
  }
  .tbs-body-type {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 12.5px;
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: var(--sl-color-white, #1e293b);
  }
  .tbs-body-note {
    margin: 0 0 0 auto;
    font-size: 10.5px;
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: var(--sl-color-gray-3, #64748b);
  }

  /* The status pill: a check on the chosen body, an en-dash on the skipped one,
     each coloured to its lit/dimmed state. */
  .tbs-status {
    margin: 0;
    flex: 0 0 auto;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 18px;
    height: 18px;
    border-radius: 999px;
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1;
  }
  .tbs-status-on {
    color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--tbs-accent) 80%, var(--sl-color-white, #1e293b));
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--tbs-accent) 22%, transparent);
  }
  .tbs-status-off {
    color: var(--sl-color-gray-3, #94a3b8);
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sl-color-gray-5, #94a3b8) 25%, transparent);
  }

  /* ── Narrow Figure: stack the stages vertically, chevrons point down ────────
     Cleaner than a flex-wrap that orphans an arrow onto its own line. */
  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    .tbs {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      row-gap: 10px;
    }
    .tbs-arrow {
      transform: rotate(90deg);
    }
    .tbs-node,
    .tbs-env {
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 260px;
    }
  }
</style>
